  "description": [
    "THf BROWN INC CMF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 15 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance WHERE THERE IS NO VISION Stalin thinks he knows wh y American and British forces in Korea have not made a better showing He says it is because the soldiers perform their duties at the front in a formal way without faith in the righteous ness of their mission and without enthusiasm This bit like most of the Stalin statement was meant primarily for home con sumption But it might well re ceive attention in the West For something can be done to improve the faith and the en thusiasm of the United Nations forces in Korea With few excep tions the troops have fought gallantly often heroically But the Korean operation lacks the simple clear appeal of homesoil defense Many soldiers grasped the ideal of UN police action but thoughtless folk cast scorn on the phrase Participation by UN members was incomplete and the debate over declaring the Red Chinese aggressors further muddied"
  ],
